rsvp.description: The MIB module to describe the RSVP Protocol

RsvpEncapsulation.name: RsvpEncapsulation
RsvpEncapsulation.description: This indicates the encapsulation that an RSVP Neighbor is perceived to be using.

RefreshInterval.name: RefreshInterval
RefreshInterval.description: The number of milliseconds that are expected to elapse between refreshes of path or reservation state. Unrefreshed Path or reservation state is removed after a small multiple of this period.

rsvpSessionNewIndex.name: rsvpSessionNewIndex
rsvpSessionNewIndex.description: This object is used to assign values to rsvpSessionNumber as described in 'Textual Conventions for SNMPv2'. The network manager reads the object, and then writes the value back in the SET that creates a new instance of rsvpSessionEntry. If the SET fails with the code 'inconsistentValue', then the process must be repeated; If the SET succeeds, then the object is incremented, and the new instance is created according to the manager's directions.

rsvpSessionTable.name: rsvpSessionTable
rsvpSessionTable.description: A table of all sessions seen by a given system.

rsvpSessionEntry.name: rsvpSessionEntry
rsvpSessionEntry.description: A single session seen by a given system.

rsvpSessionNumber.name: rsvpSessionNumber
rsvpSessionNumber.description: The number of this session. This is for SNMP Indexing purposes only and has no relation to any protocol value.

rsvpSessionType.name: rsvpSessionType
rsvpSessionType.description: The type of session (IP4, IP6, IP6 with flow information, etc).

rsvpSessionDestAddr.name: rsvpSessionDestAddr
rsvpSessionDestAddr.description: The destination address used by all senders in this session. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'active'.

rsvpSessionDestAddrLength.name: rsvpSessionDestAddrLength
rsvpSessionDestAddrLength.description: The CIDR prefix length of the session address, which is 32 for IP4 host and multicast addresses, and 128 for IP6 addresses. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'active'.

rsvpSessionProtocol.name: rsvpSessionProtocol
rsvpSessionProtocol.description: The IP Protocol used by this session. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'active'.

rsvpSessionPort.name: rsvpSessionPort
rsvpSessionPort.description: The UDP or TCP port number used as a destination port for all senders in this session. If the IP protocol in use, specified by rsvpSenderProtocol, is 50 (ESP) or 51 (AH), this represents a virtual destination port number. A value of zero indicates that the IP protocol in use does not have ports. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'active'.

rsvpSessionSenders.name: rsvpSessionSenders
rsvpSessionSenders.description: The number of distinct senders currently known to be part of this session.

rsvpSessionReceivers.name: rsvpSessionReceivers
rsvpSessionReceivers.description: The number of reservations being requested of this system for this session.

rsvpSessionRequests.name: rsvpSessionRequests
rsvpSessionRequests.description: The number of reservation requests this system is sending upstream for this session.

rsvpBadPackets.name: rsvpBadPackets
rsvpBadPackets.description: This object keeps a count of the number of bad RSVP packets received.

rsvpSenderNewIndex.name: rsvpSenderNewIndex
rsvpSenderNewIndex.description: This object is used to assign values to rsvpSenderNumber as described in 'Textual Conventions for SNMPv2'. The network manager reads the object, and then writes the value back in the SET that creates a new instance of rsvpSenderEntry. If the SET fails with the code 'inconsistentValue', then the process must be repeated; If the SET succeeds, then the object is incremented, and the new instance is created according to the manager's directions.

rsvpSenderTable.name: rsvpSenderTable
rsvpSenderTable.description: Information describing the state information displayed by senders in PATH messages.

rsvpSenderEntry.name: rsvpSenderEntry
rsvpSenderEntry.description: Information describing the state information displayed by a single sender's PATH message.

rsvpSenderNumber.name: rsvpSenderNumber
rsvpSenderNumber.description: The number of this sender. This is for SNMP Indexing purposes only and has no relation to any protocol value.

rsvpSenderType.name: rsvpSenderType
rsvpSenderType.description: The type of session (IP4, IP6, IP6 with flow information, etc).

rsvpSenderDestAddr.name: rsvpSenderDestAddr
rsvpSenderDestAddr.description: The destination address used by all senders in this session. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'active'.

rsvpSenderAddr.name: rsvpSenderAddr
rsvpSenderAddr.description: The source address used by this sender in this session. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'active'.

rsvpSenderDestAddrLength.name: rsvpSenderDestAddrLength
rsvpSenderDestAddrLength.description: The length of the destination address in bits. This is the CIDR Prefix Length, which for IP4 hosts and multicast addresses is 32 bits. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'active'.

rsvpSenderAddrLength.name: rsvpSenderAddrLength
rsvpSenderAddrLength.description: The length of the sender's address in bits. This is the CIDR Prefix Length, which for IP4 hosts and multicast addresses is 32 bits. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'active'.

rsvpSenderProtocol.name: rsvpSenderProtocol
rsvpSenderProtocol.description: The IP Protocol used by this session. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'active'.

rsvpSenderDestPort.name: rsvpSenderDestPort
rsvpSenderDestPort.description: The UDP or TCP port number used as a destination port for all senders in this session. If the IP protocol in use, specified by rsvpSenderProtocol, is 50 (ESP) or 51 (AH), this represents a virtual destination port number. A value of zero indicates that the IP protocol in use does not have ports. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'active'.

rsvpSenderPort.name: rsvpSenderPort
rsvpSenderPort.description: The UDP or TCP port number used as a source port for this sender in this session. If the IP protocol in use, specified by rsvpSenderProtocol is 50 (ESP) or 51 (AH), this represents a generalized port identifier (GPI). A value of zero indicates that the IP protocol in use does not have ports. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'active'.

rsvpSenderFlowId.name: rsvpSenderFlowId
rsvpSenderFlowId.description: The flow ID that this sender is using, if this is an IPv6 session.

rsvpSenderHopAddr.name: rsvpSenderHopAddr
rsvpSenderHopAddr.description: The address used by the previous RSVP hop (which may be the original sender).

rsvpSenderHopLih.name: rsvpSenderHopLih
rsvpSenderHopLih.description: The Logical Interface Handle used by the previous RSVP hop (which may be the original sender).

rsvpSenderInterface.name: rsvpSenderInterface
rsvpSenderInterface.description: The ifIndex value of the interface on which this PATH message was most recently received.

rsvpSenderTSpecRate.name: rsvpSenderTSpecRate
rsvpSenderTSpecRate.description: The Average Bit Rate of the sender's data stream. Within a transmission burst, the arrival rate may be as fast as rsvpSenderTSpecPeakRate (if supported by the service model); however, averaged across two or more burst intervals, the rate should not exceed rsvpSenderTSpecRate. Note that this is a prediction, often based on the general capability of a type of codec or particular encoding; the measured average rate may be significantly lower.

rsvpSenderTSpecPeakRate.name: rsvpSenderTSpecPeakRate
rsvpSenderTSpecPeakRate.description: The Peak Bit Rate of the sender's data stream. Traffic arrival is not expected to exceed this rate at any time, apart from the effects of jitter in the network. If not specified in the TSpec, this returns zero or noSuchValue.

rsvpSenderTSpecBurst.name: rsvpSenderTSpecBurst
rsvpSenderTSpecBurst.description: The size of the largest burst expected from the sender at a time.

rsvpSenderTSpecMinTU.name: rsvpSenderTSpecMinTU
rsvpSenderTSpecMinTU.description: The minimum message size for this flow. The policing algorithm will treat smaller messages as though they are this size.

rsvpSenderTSpecMaxTU.name: rsvpSenderTSpecMaxTU
rsvpSenderTSpecMaxTU.description: The maximum message size for this flow. The admission algorithm will reject TSpecs whose Maximum Transmission Unit, plus the interface headers, exceed the interface MTU.

rsvpSenderInterval.name: rsvpSenderInterval
rsvpSenderInterval.description: The interval between refresh messages as advertised by the Previous Hop.

rsvpSenderRSVPHop.name: rsvpSenderRSVPHop
rsvpSenderRSVPHop.description: If TRUE, the node believes that the previous IP hop is an RSVP hop. If FALSE, the node believes that the previous IP hop may not be an RSVP hop.

rsvpSenderLastChange.name: rsvpSenderLastChange
rsvpSenderLastChange.description: The time of the last change in this PATH message; This is either the first time it was received or the time of the most recent change in parameters.

rsvpSenderPolicy.name: rsvpSenderPolicy
rsvpSenderPolicy.description: The contents of the policy object, displayed as an uninterpreted string of octets, including the object header. In the absence of such an object, this should be of zero length.

rsvpSenderAdspecBreak.name: rsvpSenderAdspecBreak
rsvpSenderAdspecBreak.description: The global break bit general characterization parameter from the ADSPEC. If TRUE, at least one non-IS hop was detected in the path. If FALSE, no non-IS hops were detected.

rsvpSenderAdspecHopCount.name: rsvpSenderAdspecHopCount
rsvpSenderAdspecHopCount.description: The hop count general characterization parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the following conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present

rsvpSenderAdspecPathBw.name: rsvpSenderAdspecPathBw
rsvpSenderAdspecPathBw.description: The path bandwidth estimate general characterization parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the following conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present

rsvpSenderAdspecMinLatency.name: rsvpSenderAdspecMinLatency
rsvpSenderAdspecMinLatency.description: The minimum path latency general characterization parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the following conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present

rsvpSenderAdspecMtu.name: rsvpSenderAdspecMtu
rsvpSenderAdspecMtu.description: The composed Maximum Transmission Unit general characterization parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the following conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present

rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc.name: rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc
rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc.description: If TRUE, the ADSPEC contains a Guaranteed Service fragment. If FALSE, the ADSPEC does not contain a Guaranteed Service fragment.

rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedBreak.name: rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedBreak
rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedBreak.description: If TRUE, the Guaranteed Service fragment has its 'break' bit set, indicating that one or more nodes along the path do not support the guaranteed service. If FALSE, and rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc is TRUE, the 'break' bit is not set. If rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc is FALSE, this returns FALSE or noSuchValue.

rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedCtot.name: rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedCtot
rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedCtot.description: If rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc is TRUE, this is the end-to-end composed value for the guaranteed service 'C' parameter. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the following conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue.

rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedDtot.name: rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedDtot
rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedDtot.description: If rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc is TRUE, this is the end-to-end composed value for the guaranteed service 'D' parameter. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the following conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue.

rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedCsum.name: rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedCsum
rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedCsum.description: If rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc is TRUE, this is the composed value for the guaranteed service 'C' parameter since the last reshaping point. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the following conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue.

rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedDsum.name: rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedDsum
rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedDsum.description: If rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc is TRUE, this is the composed value for the guaranteed service 'D' parameter since the last reshaping point. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the following conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue.

rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedHopCount.name: rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedHopCount
rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedHopCount.description: If rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc is TRUE, this is the service-specific override of the hop count general characterization parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the following conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue.

rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedPathBw.name: rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedPathBw
rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedPathBw.description: If rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc is TRUE, this is the service-specific override of the path bandwidth estimate general characterization parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the following conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue.

rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedMinLatency.name: rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedMinLatency
rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedMinLatency.description: If rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc is TRUE, this is the service-specific override of the minimum path latency general characterization parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the following conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue.

rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedMtu.name: rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedMtu
rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedMtu.description: If rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc is TRUE, this is the service-specific override of the composed Maximum Transmission Unit general characterization parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the following conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If rsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue.

rsvpSenderAdspecCtrlLoadSvc.name: rsvpSenderAdspecCtrlLoadSvc
rsvpSenderAdspecCtrlLoadSvc.description: If TRUE, the ADSPEC contains a Controlled Load Service fragment. If FALSE, the ADSPEC does not contain a Controlled Load Service fragment.

rsvpSenderAdspecCtrlLoadBreak.name: rsvpSenderAdspecCtrlLoadBreak
rsvpSenderAdspecCtrlLoadBreak.description: If TRUE, the Controlled Load Service fragment has its 'break' bit set, indicating that one or more nodes along the path do not support the controlled load service. If FALSE, and rsvpSenderAdspecCtrlLoadSvc is TRUE, the 'break' bit is not set. If rsvpSenderAdspecCtrlLoadSvc is FALSE, this returns FALSE or noSuchValue.

rsvpSenderAdspecCtrlLoadHopCount.name: rsvpSenderAdspecCtrlLoadHopCount
rsvpSenderAdspecCtrlLoadHopCount.description: If rsvpSenderAdspecCtrlLoadSvc is TRUE, this is the service-specific override of the hop count general characterization parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the following conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If rsvpSenderAdspecCtrlLoadSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue.

rsvpSenderAdspecCtrlLoadPathBw.name: rsvpSenderAdspecCtrlLoadPathBw
rsvpSenderAdspecCtrlLoadPathBw.description: If rsvpSenderAdspecCtrlLoadSvc is TRUE, this is the service-specific override of the path bandwidth estimate general characterization parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the following conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If rsvpSenderAdspecCtrlLoadSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue.

rsvpSenderAdspecCtrlLoadMinLatency.name: rsvpSenderAdspecCtrlLoadMinLatency
rsvpSenderAdspecCtrlLoadMinLatency.description: If rsvpSenderAdspecCtrlLoadSvc is TRUE, this is the service-specific override of the minimum path latency general characterization parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the following conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If rsvpSenderAdspecCtrlLoadSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue.

rsvpSenderAdspecCtrlLoadMtu.name: rsvpSenderAdspecCtrlLoadMtu
rsvpSenderAdspecCtrlLoadMtu.description: If rsvpSenderAdspecCtrlLoadSvc is TRUE, this is the service-specific override of the composed Maximum Transmission Unit general characterization parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the following conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If rsvpSenderAdspecCtrlLoadSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue.

rsvpSenderStatus.name: rsvpSenderStatus
rsvpSenderStatus.description: 'active' for all active PATH messages. This object may be used to install static PATH information or delete PATH information.

rsvpSenderTTL.name: rsvpSenderTTL
rsvpSenderTTL.description: The TTL value in the RSVP header that was last received.

rsvpSenderOutInterfaceTable.name: rsvpSenderOutInterfaceTable
rsvpSenderOutInterfaceTable.description: List of outgoing interfaces that PATH messages use. The ifIndex is the ifIndex value of the egress interface.

rsvpSenderOutInterfaceEntry.name: rsvpSenderOutInterfaceEntry
rsvpSenderOutInterfaceEntry.description: List of outgoing interfaces that a particular PATH message has.

rsvpResvNewIndex.name: rsvpResvNewIndex
rsvpResvNewIndex.description: This object is used to assign values to rsvpResvNumber as described in 'Textual Conventions for SNMPv2'. The network manager reads the object, and then writes the value back in the SET that creates a new instance of rsvpResvEntry. If the SET fails with the code 'inconsistentValue', then the process must be repeated; If the SET succeeds, then the object is incremented, and the new instance is created according to the manager's directions.

rsvpResvTable.name: rsvpResvTable
rsvpResvTable.description: Information describing the state information displayed by receivers in RESV messages.

rsvpResvEntry.name: rsvpResvEntry
rsvpResvEntry.description: Information describing the state information displayed by a single receiver's RESV message concerning a single sender.

rsvpResvNumber.name: rsvpResvNumber
rsvpResvNumber.description: The number of this reservation request. This is for SNMP Indexing purposes only and has no relation to any protocol value.

rsvpResvType.name: rsvpResvType
rsvpResvType.description: The type of session (IP4, IP6, IP6 with flow information, etc).

rsvpResvDestAddr.name: rsvpResvDestAddr
rsvpResvDestAddr.description: The destination address used by all senders in this session. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'active'.

rsvpResvSenderAddr.name: rsvpResvSenderAddr
rsvpResvSenderAddr.description: The source address of the sender selected by this reservation. The value of all zeroes indicates 'all senders'. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'active'.

rsvpResvDestAddrLength.name: rsvpResvDestAddrLength
rsvpResvDestAddrLength.description: The length of the destination address in bits. This is the CIDR Prefix Length, which for IP4 hosts and multicast addresses is 32 bits. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'active'.

rsvpResvSenderAddrLength.name: rsvpResvSenderAddrLength
rsvpResvSenderAddrLength.description: The length of the sender's address in bits. This is the CIDR Prefix Length, which for IP4 hosts and multicast addresses is 32 bits. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'active'.

rsvpResvProtocol.name: rsvpResvProtocol
rsvpResvProtocol.description: The IP Protocol used by this session. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'active'.

rsvpResvDestPort.name: rsvpResvDestPort
rsvpResvDestPort.description: The UDP or TCP port number used as a destination port for all senders in this session. If the IP protocol in use, specified by rsvpResvProtocol, is 50 (ESP) or 51 (AH), this represents a virtual destination port number. A value of zero indicates that the IP protocol in use does not have ports. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'active'.

rsvpResvPort.name: rsvpResvPort
rsvpResvPort.description: The UDP or TCP port number used as a source port for this sender in this session. If the IP protocol in use, specified by rsvpResvProtocol is 50 (ESP) or 51 (AH), this represents a generalized port identifier (GPI). A value of zero indicates that the IP protocol in use does not have ports. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'active'.

rsvpResvHopAddr.name: rsvpResvHopAddr
rsvpResvHopAddr.description: The address used by the next RSVP hop (which may be the ultimate receiver).

rsvpResvHopLih.name: rsvpResvHopLih
rsvpResvHopLih.description: The Logical Interface Handle received from the previous RSVP hop (which may be the ultimate receiver).

rsvpResvInterface.name: rsvpResvInterface
rsvpResvInterface.description: The ifIndex value of the interface on which this RESV message was most recently received.

rsvpResvService.name: rsvpResvService
rsvpResvService.description: The QoS Service classification requested by the receiver.

rsvpResvTSpecRate.name: rsvpResvTSpecRate
rsvpResvTSpecRate.description: The Average Bit Rate of the sender's data stream. Within a transmission burst, the arrival rate may be as fast as rsvpResvTSpecPeakRate (if supported by the service model); however, averaged across two or more burst intervals, the rate should not exceed rsvpResvTSpecRate. Note that this is a prediction, often based on the general capability of a type of codec or particular encoding; the measured average rate may be significantly lower.

rsvpResvTSpecPeakRate.name: rsvpResvTSpecPeakRate
rsvpResvTSpecPeakRate.description: The Peak Bit Rate of the sender's data stream. Traffic arrival is not expected to exceed this rate at any time, apart from the effects of jitter in the network. If not specified in the TSpec, this returns zero or noSuchValue.

rsvpResvTSpecBurst.name: rsvpResvTSpecBurst
rsvpResvTSpecBurst.description: The size of the largest burst expected from the sender at a time. If this is less than the sender's advertised burst size, the receiver is asking the network to provide flow pacing beyond what would be provided under normal circumstances. Such pacing is at the network's option.

rsvpResvTSpecMinTU.name: rsvpResvTSpecMinTU
rsvpResvTSpecMinTU.description: The minimum message size for this flow. The policing algorithm will treat smaller messages as though they are this size.

rsvpResvTSpecMaxTU.name: rsvpResvTSpecMaxTU
rsvpResvTSpecMaxTU.description: The maximum message size for this flow. The admission algorithm will reject TSpecs whose Maximum Transmission Unit, plus the interface headers, exceed the interface MTU.

rsvpResvRSpecRate.name: rsvpResvRSpecRate
rsvpResvRSpecRate.description: If the requested service is Guaranteed, as specified by rsvpResvService, this is the clearing rate that is being requested. Otherwise, it is zero, or the agent may return noSuchValue.

rsvpResvRSpecSlack.name: rsvpResvRSpecSlack
rsvpResvRSpecSlack.description: If the requested service is Guaranteed, as specified by rsvpResvService, this is the delay slack. Otherwise, it is zero, or the agent may return noSuchValue.

rsvpResvInterval.name: rsvpResvInterval
rsvpResvInterval.description: The interval between refresh messages as advertised by the Next Hop.

rsvpResvScope.name: rsvpResvScope
rsvpResvScope.description: The contents of the scope object, displayed as an uninterpreted string of octets, including the object header. In the absence of such an object, this should be of zero length. If the length is non-zero, this contains a series of IP4 or IP6 addresses.

rsvpResvShared.name: rsvpResvShared
rsvpResvShared.description: If TRUE, a reservation shared among senders is requested. If FALSE, a reservation specific to this sender is requested.

rsvpResvExplicit.name: rsvpResvExplicit
rsvpResvExplicit.description: If TRUE, individual senders are listed using Filter Specifications. If FALSE, all senders are implicitly selected. The Scope Object will contain a list of senders that need to receive this reservation request for the purpose of routing the RESV message.

rsvpResvRSVPHop.name: rsvpResvRSVPHop
rsvpResvRSVPHop.description: If TRUE, the node believes that the previous IP hop is an RSVP hop. If FALSE, the node believes that the previous IP hop may not be an RSVP hop.

rsvpResvLastChange.name: rsvpResvLastChange
rsvpResvLastChange.description: The time of the last change in this reservation request; This is either the first time it was received or the time of the most recent change in parameters.

rsvpResvPolicy.name: rsvpResvPolicy
rsvpResvPolicy.description: The contents of the policy object, displayed as an uninterpreted string of octets, including the object header. In the absence of such an object, this should be of zero length.

rsvpResvStatus.name: rsvpResvStatus
rsvpResvStatus.description: 'active' for all active RESV messages. This object may be used to install static RESV information or delete RESV information.

rsvpResvTTL.name: rsvpResvTTL
rsvpResvTTL.description: The TTL value in the RSVP header that was last received.

rsvpResvFlowId.name: rsvpResvFlowId
rsvpResvFlowId.description: The flow ID that this receiver is using, if this is an IPv6 session.

rsvpResvFwdNewIndex.name: rsvpResvFwdNewIndex
rsvpResvFwdNewIndex.description: This object is used to assign values to rsvpResvFwdNumber as described in 'Textual Conventions for SNMPv2'. The network manager reads the object, and then writes the value back in the SET that creates a new instance of rsvpResvFwdEntry. If the SET fails with the code 'inconsistentValue', then the process must be repeated; If the SET succeeds, then the object is incremented, and the new instance is created according to the manager's directions.

rsvpResvFwdTable.name: rsvpResvFwdTable
rsvpResvFwdTable.description: Information describing the state information displayed upstream in RESV messages.

rsvpResvFwdEntry.name: rsvpResvFwdEntry
rsvpResvFwdEntry.description: Information describing the state information displayed upstream in an RESV message concerning a single sender.

rsvpResvFwdNumber.name: rsvpResvFwdNumber
rsvpResvFwdNumber.description: The number of this reservation request. This is for SNMP Indexing purposes only and has no relation to any protocol value.

rsvpResvFwdType.name: rsvpResvFwdType
rsvpResvFwdType.description: The type of session (IP4, IP6, IP6 with flow information, etc).

rsvpResvFwdDestAddr.name: rsvpResvFwdDestAddr
rsvpResvFwdDestAddr.description: The destination address used by all senders in this session. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'active'.

rsvpResvFwdSenderAddr.name: rsvpResvFwdSenderAddr
rsvpResvFwdSenderAddr.description: The source address of the sender selected by this reservation. The value of all zeroes indicates 'all senders'. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'active'.

rsvpResvFwdDestAddrLength.name: rsvpResvFwdDestAddrLength
rsvpResvFwdDestAddrLength.description: The length of the destination address in bits. This is the CIDR Prefix Length, which for IP4 hosts and multicast addresses is 32 bits. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'active'.

rsvpResvFwdSenderAddrLength.name: rsvpResvFwdSenderAddrLength
rsvpResvFwdSenderAddrLength.description: The length of the sender's address in bits. This is the CIDR Prefix Length, which for IP4 hosts and multicast addresses is 32 bits. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'active'.

rsvpResvFwdProtocol.name: rsvpResvFwdProtocol
rsvpResvFwdProtocol.description: The IP Protocol used by a session. for secure sessions, this indicates IP Security. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'active'.

rsvpResvFwdDestPort.name: rsvpResvFwdDestPort
rsvpResvFwdDestPort.description: The UDP or TCP port number used as a destination port for all senders in this session. If the IP protocol in use, specified by rsvpResvFwdProtocol, is 50 (ESP) or 51 (AH), this represents a virtual destination port number. A value of zero indicates that the IP protocol in use does not have ports. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'active'.

rsvpResvFwdPort.name: rsvpResvFwdPort
rsvpResvFwdPort.description: The UDP or TCP port number used as a source port for this sender in this session. If the IP protocol in use, specified by rsvpResvFwdProtocol is 50 (ESP) or 51 (AH), this represents a generalized port identifier (GPI). A value of zero indicates that the IP protocol in use does not have ports. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'active'.

rsvpResvFwdHopAddr.name: rsvpResvFwdHopAddr
rsvpResvFwdHopAddr.description: The address of the (previous) RSVP that will receive this message.

rsvpResvFwdHopLih.name: rsvpResvFwdHopLih
rsvpResvFwdHopLih.description: The Logical Interface Handle sent to the (previous) RSVP that will receive this message.

rsvpResvFwdInterface.name: rsvpResvFwdInterface
rsvpResvFwdInterface.description: The ifIndex value of the interface on which this RESV message was most recently sent.

rsvpResvFwdTSpecRate.name: rsvpResvFwdTSpecRate
rsvpResvFwdTSpecRate.description: The Average Bit Rate of the sender's data stream. Within a transmission burst, the arrival rate may be as fast as rsvpResvFwdTSpecPeakRate (if supported by the service model); however, averaged across two or more burst intervals, the rate should not exceed rsvpResvFwdTSpecRate. Note that this is a prediction, often based on the general capability of a type of codec or particular encoding; the measured average rate may be significantly lower.

rsvpResvFwdTSpecPeakRate.name: rsvpResvFwdTSpecPeakRate
rsvpResvFwdTSpecPeakRate.description: The Peak Bit Rate of the sender's data stream Traffic arrival is not expected to exceed this rate at any time, apart from the effects of jitter in the network. If not specified in the TSpec, this returns zero or noSuchValue.

rsvpResvFwdTSpecBurst.name: rsvpResvFwdTSpecBurst
rsvpResvFwdTSpecBurst.description: The size of the largest burst expected from the sender at a time. If this is less than the sender's advertised burst size, the receiver is asking the network to provide flow pacing beyond what would be provided under normal circumstances. Such pacing is at the network's option.

rsvpResvFwdTSpecMinTU.name: rsvpResvFwdTSpecMinTU
rsvpResvFwdTSpecMinTU.description: The minimum message size for this flow. The policing algorithm will treat smaller messages as though they are this size.

rsvpResvFwdTSpecMaxTU.name: rsvpResvFwdTSpecMaxTU
rsvpResvFwdTSpecMaxTU.description: The maximum message size for this flow. The admission algorithm will reject TSpecs whose Maximum Transmission Unit, plus the interface headers, exceed the interface MTU.

rsvpResvFwdRSpecRate.name: rsvpResvFwdRSpecRate
rsvpResvFwdRSpecRate.description: If the requested service is Guaranteed, as specified by rsvpResvService, this is the clearing rate that is being requested. Otherwise, it is zero, or the agent may return noSuchValue.

rsvpResvFwdRSpecSlack.name: rsvpResvFwdRSpecSlack
rsvpResvFwdRSpecSlack.description: If the requested service is Guaranteed, as specified by rsvpResvService, this is the delay slack. Otherwise, it is zero, or the agent may return noSuchValue.

rsvpResvFwdInterval.name: rsvpResvFwdInterval
rsvpResvFwdInterval.description: The interval between refresh messages advertised to the Previous Hop.

rsvpResvFwdScope.name: rsvpResvFwdScope
rsvpResvFwdScope.description: The contents of the scope object, displayed as an uninterpreted string of octets, including the object header. In the absence of such an object, this should be of zero length.

rsvpResvFwdShared.name: rsvpResvFwdShared
rsvpResvFwdShared.description: If TRUE, a reservation shared among senders is requested. If FALSE, a reservation specific to this sender is requested.

rsvpResvFwdExplicit.name: rsvpResvFwdExplicit
rsvpResvFwdExplicit.description: If TRUE, individual senders are listed using Filter Specifications. If FALSE, all senders are implicitly selected. The Scope Object will contain a list of senders that need to receive this reservation request for the purpose of routing the RESV message.

rsvpResvFwdRSVPHop.name: rsvpResvFwdRSVPHop
rsvpResvFwdRSVPHop.description: If TRUE, the node believes that the next IP hop is an RSVP hop. If FALSE, the node believes that the next IP hop may not be an RSVP hop.

rsvpResvFwdLastChange.name: rsvpResvFwdLastChange
rsvpResvFwdLastChange.description: The time of the last change in this request; This is either the first time it was sent or the time of the most recent change in parameters.

rsvpResvFwdPolicy.name: rsvpResvFwdPolicy
rsvpResvFwdPolicy.description: The contents of the policy object, displayed as an uninterpreted string of octets, including the object header. In the absence of such an object, this should be of zero length.

rsvpResvFwdStatus.name: rsvpResvFwdStatus
rsvpResvFwdStatus.description: 'active' for all active RESV messages. This object may be used to delete RESV information.

rsvpResvFwdTTL.name: rsvpResvFwdTTL
rsvpResvFwdTTL.description: The TTL value in the RSVP header that was last received.

rsvpResvFwdFlowId.name: rsvpResvFwdFlowId
rsvpResvFwdFlowId.description: The flow ID that this receiver is using, if this is an IPv6 session.

rsvpIfTable.name: rsvpIfTable
rsvpIfTable.description: The RSVP-specific attributes of the system's interfaces.

rsvpIfEntry.name: rsvpIfEntry
rsvpIfEntry.description: The RSVP-specific attributes of the a given interface.

rsvpIfUdpNbrs.name: rsvpIfUdpNbrs
rsvpIfUdpNbrs.description: The number of neighbors perceived to be using only the RSVP UDP Encapsulation.

rsvpIfIpNbrs.name: rsvpIfIpNbrs
rsvpIfIpNbrs.description: The number of neighbors perceived to be using only the RSVP IP Encapsulation.

rsvpIfNbrs.name: rsvpIfNbrs
rsvpIfNbrs.description: The number of neighbors currently perceived; this will exceed rsvpIfIpNbrs + rsvpIfUdpNbrs by the number of neighbors using both encapsulations.

rsvpIfRefreshBlockadeMultiple.name: rsvpIfRefreshBlockadeMultiple
rsvpIfRefreshBlockadeMultiple.description: The value of the RSVP value 'Kb', Which is the minimum number of refresh intervals that blockade state will last once entered.

rsvpIfRefreshMultiple.name: rsvpIfRefreshMultiple
rsvpIfRefreshMultiple.description: The value of the RSVP value 'K', which is the number of refresh intervals which must elapse (minimum) before a PATH or RESV message which is not being refreshed will be aged out.

rsvpIfTTL.name: rsvpIfTTL
rsvpIfTTL.description: The value of SEND_TTL used on this interface for messages this node originates. If set to zero, the node determines the TTL via other means.

rsvpIfRefreshInterval.name: rsvpIfRefreshInterval
rsvpIfRefreshInterval.description: The value of the RSVP value 'R', which is the minimum period between refresh transmissions of a given PATH or RESV message on an interface.

rsvpIfRouteDelay.name: rsvpIfRouteDelay
rsvpIfRouteDelay.description: The approximate period from the time a route is changed to the time a resulting message appears on the interface.

rsvpIfEnabled.name: rsvpIfEnabled
rsvpIfEnabled.description: If TRUE, RSVP is enabled on this Interface. If FALSE, RSVP is not enabled on this interface.

rsvpIfUdpRequired.name: rsvpIfUdpRequired
rsvpIfUdpRequired.description: If TRUE, manual configuration forces the use of UDP encapsulation on the interface. If FALSE, UDP encapsulation is only used if rsvpIfUdpNbrs is not zero.

rsvpIfStatus.name: rsvpIfStatus
rsvpIfStatus.description: 'active' on interfaces that are configured for RSVP.

rsvpNbrTable.name: rsvpNbrTable
rsvpNbrTable.description: Information describing the Neighbors of an RSVP system.

rsvpNbrEntry.name: rsvpNbrEntry
rsvpNbrEntry.description: Information describing a single RSVP Neighbor.

rsvpNbrAddress.name: rsvpNbrAddress
rsvpNbrAddress.description: The IP4 or IP6 Address used by this neighbor. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'active'.

rsvpNbrProtocol.name: rsvpNbrProtocol
rsvpNbrProtocol.description: The encapsulation being used by this neighbor.

rsvpNbrStatus.name: rsvpNbrStatus
rsvpNbrStatus.description: 'active' for all neighbors. This object may be used to configure neighbors. In the presence of configured neighbors, the implementation may (but is not required to) limit the set of valid neighbors to those configured.

newFlow.name: newFlow
newFlow.description: The newFlow trap indicates that the originating system has installed a new flow in its classifier, or (when reservation authorization is in view) is prepared to install such a flow in the classifier and is requesting authorization. The objects included with the Notification may be used to read further information using the Integrated Services and RSVP MIBs. Authorization or non- authorization may be enacted by a write to the variable intSrvFlowStatus.

lostFlow.name: lostFlow
lostFlow.description: The lostFlow trap indicates that the originating system has removed a flow from its classifier.

rsvpCompliance.name: rsvpCompliance
rsvpCompliance.description: The compliance statement. Note that the implementation of this module requires implementation of the Integrated Services MIB as well.

rsvpSessionGroup.name: rsvpSessionGroup
rsvpSessionGroup.description: These objects are required for RSVP Systems.

rsvpSenderGroup.name: rsvpSenderGroup
rsvpSenderGroup.description: These objects are required for RSVP Systems.

rsvpResvGroup.name: rsvpResvGroup
rsvpResvGroup.description: These objects are required for RSVP Systems.

rsvpResvFwdGroup.name: rsvpResvFwdGroup
rsvpResvFwdGroup.description: These objects are optional, used for some RSVP Systems.

rsvpIfGroup.name: rsvpIfGroup
rsvpIfGroup.description: These objects are required for RSVP Systems.

rsvpNbrGroup.name: rsvpNbrGroup
rsvpNbrGroup.description: These objects are required for RSVP Systems.

rsvpGenObjectsGroup.name: rsvpGenObjectsGroup
rsvpGenObjectsGroup.description: This objects are required for RSVP Systems.

rsvpSenderOutInterfaceGroup.name: rsvpSenderOutInterfaceGroup
rsvpSenderOutInterfaceGroup.description: These objects are required for RSVP Systems.

rsvpNotificationGroup.name: rsvpNotificationGroup
rsvpNotificationGroup.description: This notification is required for Systems supporting the RSVP Policy Module using an SNMP interface to the Policy Manager.
